{"title_page": "Baywatch (film)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Baywatch\n| image = Baywatch poster.jpg\n| alt =\n| caption = Theatrical release poster\n| director = [[Seth Gordon]]\n| producer = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Ivan Reitman]]\n* [[Michael Berk]]\n* [[Douglas Schwartz]]\n* [[Gregory J. Bonann]]\n* [[Beau Flynn]]\n}}\n| screenplay = {{Unbulleted list|[[Mark Swift and Damian Shannon|Damian Shannon<br>Mark Swift]]}}\n| story = {{Unbulleted list|Jay Scherick|David Ronn|[[Thomas Lennon]]|[[Robert Ben Garant]]}}\n| based on = {{Based on|''[[Baywatch]]''|Michael Berk<br />Douglas Schwartz<br />Gregory J. Bonann}}\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Dwayne Johnson]]\n* [[Zac Efron]]\n* [[Alexandra Daddario]]\n* [[Priyanka Chopra]] <!-- per billing block imp poster 15, see talk page -->\n* [[David Hasselhoff]] <!-- per billing block imp poster 15, see talk page -->\n}}\n| music = [[Christopher Lennertz]]\n| cinematography = [[Eric Steelberg]]\n| editing = Peter S. Elliot\n| production companies = {{plainlist|\n* [[Paramount Pictures]]<ref name=insight>{{cite web|url=http://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|title=Film releases|work=[[Variety Insight]]|accessdate=May 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170218043334/http://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|archive-date=February 18, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* Contrafilm<ref name=insight/>\n* [[The Montecito Picture Company]]<ref name=insight/>\n* Vinson Pictures<ref name=insight/>\n* [[Seven Bucks Productions]]<ref name=insight/>\n* Flynn Company<ref name=insight/>\n* Cold Spring Pictures<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/executive-suite-tom-pollock-ivan-165068 |title=Executive Suite: Tom Pollock and Ivan Reitman |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=October 3, 2011 |accessdate=January 25, 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n| distributor = Paramount Pictures<ref name=insight/>\n| released = {{Film date|2017|5|13|[[Miami]]|2017|5|25|United States}}\n| runtime = 116 minutes<ref name=\"BOM\" />\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| budget = $65\u201369 million<ref name=2017FFS/><ref name=\"BOM\" />\n| gross = $177.9 million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=baywatch.htm|title=Baywatch (2017)|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=September 10, 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Baywatch''''' is a 2017 American [[action comedy]] film based on [[Baywatch|the television series]] created by Michael Berk, Douglas Schwartz, and Gregory J. Bonann. The film was directed by [[Seth Gordon]], written by [[Mark Swift and Damian Shannon]] (from a story by Jay Scherick, David Ronn, [[Thomas Lennon]], and [[Robert Ben Garant]]), and stars [[Dwayne Johnson]], [[Zac Efron]], [[Jon Bass (actor)|Jon Bass]], [[Alexandra Daddario]], [[Kelly Rohrbach]] and [[Priyanka Chopra]]. The story follows lifeguard [[Mitch Buchannon]] and his team who must take down a drug lord in an effort to save their beach.\n\n[[Principal photography]] began on February 22, 2016, in [[Florida]] and [[Savannah, Georgia]]. The film was released in the United States on May 25, 2017, by [[Paramount Pictures]], grossed $177 million worldwide and received negative reviews from critics, with criticism for its crude humor, storyline, and character development, but Johnson did receive some praise.<ref name=\"thr-roundup\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/baywatch-movie-reviews-roundup-1007039|title=\u2018'Baywatch': What the Critics Are Saying|author= Lauren Huff|work= [[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=May 23, 2017|accessdate=January 1, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"opening\" /> ''Baywatch'' received five nominations at the [[38th Golden Raspberry Awards]], including [[Golden Raspberry Award for Worst Picture|Worst Picture]] and [[Golden Raspberry Award for Worst Actor|Worst Actor]] for Efron.<ref name=\"razzies\" />\n\n==Plot==\nIn Emerald Bay, [[Florida]], Lt. Mitch Buchannon and his team of lifeguards, including second-in-command Stephanie Holden and veteran C.J. Parker, protect the beaches and the bay as part of an elite division known as Baywatch. Having made over 500 rescues in his career, Mitch is beloved by the community, to the annoyance of local beat cop Garner Ellerbee and Mitch's superior, Captain Thorpe. During one of his morning patrols, Mitch finds a small pouch of [[flakka]] drug washed up near the Huntley Club, which is now under the ownership of businesswoman Victoria Leeds, who has been secretly bribing city councilman Rodriguez and others in efforts to increase her stake in the bay.\n\nMitch later meets Olympian Matt Brody who, thinking his [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] position entitles him to be on the team without trying out, says that he is already on the team. He then calls Holden in, and they tease Brody. Mitch later makes Brody beat him on the \"big boys'\" course. When the course ends, a mom and her kids start drowning, resulting in the lifeguards and Brody rushing to save them, even though Brody isn't a lifeguard yet. When everything's clear, the results of the tryouts are in, and the people who made it are Ronnie Greenbaum, Summer Quinn, and Matt Brody. \n\nWhen a private yacht catches fire, Brody disobeys orders and dives directly under the flames, causing Holden and C. J. to have to save him. The occupants are evacuated, except for the deceased councilman Rodriguez. Ellerbee disapproves of Mitch's further investigative actions. Mitch and the gang attend a party held by Leeds to investigate about the [[Alpha-Pyrrolidinopentiophenone|flakka]], but without much luck, as Brody makes a fool of himself getting drunk. Mitch, Brody, and Summer later infiltrate the hospital morgue, where they record two of Leeds' henchmen planting a falsified autopsy report to cover up the fact that Rodriguez was murdered on her orders. Unfortunately, they are discovered, and though Mitch manages to subdue and capture one of them, the recording is destroyed and Ellerbee is forced to release their suspect on a lack of evidence. Angered, Thorpe threatens to fire Mitch if he oversteps his authority again.\n\nConvinced that Leeds is running drugs out of the Huntley, Mitch and Brody go undercover and sneak into the club kitchen, where they witness her workers retrieving the drugs from barrels of fish and processing them. They contact Ellerbee, only to learn that another dead body has been found on the beach. Thorpe, enraged that Mitch essentially deserted his post, fires him and names Brody as the new lieutenant. Brody doesn't want the job, but he is forced to take it. Mitch then takes a job as a salesman at [[Sprint Corporation|Sprint]].\n\nBrody later sees a \"sand grifter (beach thief)\" steal bags using a cooler. He later intercepts the man and steals the cooler. After finding another pouch of [[Alpha-Pyrrolidinopentiophenone|flakka]] on the beach, Brody steals the second victim's report from Ellerbee using the cooler and brings it to Summer, who confirms his suspicion that the man was killed by a knife instead of a shark attack. Ronnie, upon recognizing the victim as his friend Dave, helps Brody hack into Leeds' servers, revealing her plan to privatize the entire beach by systematically buying out or eliminating every competing business owner.\n\nThe team later infiltrates a private party on Leeds' personal yacht, discovering how she's been using the hull to smuggle the drugs. Brody is captured and placed in a bait cage to be drowned, and a gloating Leeds reveals that she bribed Thorpe to fire Mitch and put Brody for the job before pushing the cage into the water. Just before Brody dies, Summer swims up to him and gives him the kiss of life. However, this turns out to be a hallucination when he regains consciousness and realizes it is actually Mitch resuscitating him. The two catch up to Leeds, while Ronnie and C. J. hack the system and launch fireworks to prevent her escape helicopter from landing. Just as they run out, a wounded Mitch, having intentionally stung himself with a [[sea urchin]] to boost his adrenaline, uses a [[Roman candle (firework)|Roman candle]] to blow Leeds up, saving Brody once again. Ellerbee arrives and takes Leeds' henchmen into custody, apologizing to Mitch for doubting him. Thorpe arrives and begins to berate Mitch for not understanding he's fired and returning to the beach. In response, Brody punches Thorpe in the face. Thorpe is subsequently arrested for his role in Leeds' plan.\n\nIn the aftermath, Ronnie and Brody begin relationships with C.J. and Summer respectively. Mitch, having been reinstated, no longer makes Summer, Ronnie, and Brody trainees and introduces them to their new captain, [[Pamela Anderson|Casey Jean]].\n\n== Cast ==\n<!-- opening title card order at start of film, role names per closing credits -->\n* [[Dwayne Johnson]] as [[Mitch Buchannon]]\n* [[Zac Efron]] as Matt Brody\n* [[Priyanka Chopra]] as Victoria Leeds \n* [[Alexandra Daddario]] as Summer Quinn\n* [[Jon Bass (actor)|Jon Bass]] as Ronnie Greenbaum\n* [[Hannibal Buress]] as Dave the Tech\n* [[Kelly Rohrbach]] as [[C. J. Parker]]\n* [[Ilfenesh Hadera]] as Stephanie Holden\n* [[Yahya Abdul-Mateen II]] as Sgt. Ellerbee\n* [[Oscar Nunez]] as Councilman Rodriguez\n* [[Rob Huebel]] as Captain Thorpe\n* [[Amin Joseph]] as Frankie\n* [[Jack Kesy]] as Leon\n* [[Pamela Anderson]] as Casey Jean Parker<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.msn.com/en-us/movies/news/pamela-anderson-joins-dwayne-johnson%E2%80%99s-%E2%80%98baywatch%E2%80%99-movie/ar-BBs6woC?ocid=ansmsnent11|title=Pamela Anderson Joins Dwayne Johnson's 'Baywatch' Movie|work=msn.com|accessdate=July 19, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160507161351/http://www.msn.com/en-us/movies/news/pamela-anderson-joins-dwayne-johnson%E2%80%99s-%E2%80%98baywatch%E2%80%99-movie/ar-BBs6woC?ocid=ansmsnent11|archive-date=May 7, 2016|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/DwayneJohnson/videos/10154185279449384/|title=Dwayne The Rock Johnson \u2013 Timeline |work=Facebook|accessdate=July 19, 2016}}</ref>\n<!-- title card \"and\" credit -->\n* [[David Hasselhoff]] as Mitch, The Mentor\n\n== Production ==\nA ''Baywatch'' movie was first announced in 2004, although the movie became stuck in [[development hell]] over the years, with multiple writers penning drafts.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Brown|first1=Kat|title=Baywatch at last! Horrible Bosses' Seth Gordon set to direct Dwayne Johnson|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/film/baywatch/seth-gordon-dwayne-johnson/|website=Telegrap|accessdate=July 27, 2017}}</ref> In July 2015, [[Sean Anders]] was replaced by [[Seth Gordon]] as director.<ref name=July2015Variety>{{cite news|last1=Kroll|first1=Justin|title=Seth Gordon to Direct Dwayne Johnson in Paramount\u2019s \u2018Baywatch\u2019 Movie|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/seth-gordon-to-direct-dwayne-johnson-in-paramounts-baywatch-movie-1201544299/|accessdate=July 25, 2015|work=variety.com|date=July 23, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dwayne Johnson\u2019s \u2018Baywatch\u2019&nbsp;Movie Lands a Director|url=http://screencrush.com/dwayne-johnson-baywatch-seth-gordon/|website=ScreenCrush.com|accessdate=August 21, 2017}}</ref> On October 2, 2014, [[Dwayne Johnson]] was attached to star in the lead role, and Justin Malen was set to rewrite the script.<ref name=Johnson>{{cite news|last1=Siegel|first1=Tatiana|title=Paramount Moves Forward With 'Baywatch' Movie|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/paramount-moves-forward-baywatch-movie-707530|accessdate=October 3, 2014|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=October 2, 2014}}</ref> Damian Shannon and Mark Swift wrote the latest draft, and the film would be comedic in style.<ref name=\"July2015Variety\" /> On August 10, 2015, [[Zac Efron]] signed on to star in the film, and [[Beau Flynn]] and [[Ivan Reitman]] joined to produce with Johnson's Seven Bucks Productions.<ref name=EfronCast>{{cite news|last1=Kit|first1=Borys|title=Zac Efron in Talks to Star With Dwayne Johnson in 'Baywatch' Movie (Exclusive)|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/baywatch-movie-zac-efron-talks-814159|accessdate=August 11, 2015|work=hollywoodreporter.com|date=August 10, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Verhoeven|first=Beatrice|title=Zac Efron\u2019s \u2018Baywatch\u2019 Character Is Basically Ryan Lochte (Exclusive)|url=http://www.thewrap.com/zac-efron-baywatch-character-ryan-lochte-olympic-swimmer/|accessdate=August 11, 2015|work=The Wrap|date=August 29, 2016}}</ref> On November 9, 2015, ''[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]'' reported that seven actresses were among the short list testing for the lead female role, [[Alexandra Daddario]], [[Ashley Benson]], [[Nina Dobrev]], [[Alexandra Shipp]], [[Shelley Hennig]], [[Bianca A. Santos]], and [[Denyse Tontz]].<ref>{{cite news |last= Fleming Jr |first= Mike |title= Bevy Of Actresses Test For \u2018Baywatch\u2019 Lead; Dwayne Johnson & Zac Efron Star |url= http://deadline.com/2015/11/baywatch-actresses-shortlist-alexandra-daddario-ashley-benson-nina-dobrev-alexandra-shipp-bianca-santos-1201615126/ |accessdate= November 10, 2015 |website= [[Deadline Hollywood]] |date= November 9, 2015 }}</ref> On November 18, 2015, Johnson confirmed Daddario would play Summer, a lifeguard, and the love interest of Efron's character.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dwayne Johnson on Instagram|url=https://instagram.com/p/-O5YV-Ih3H/|publisher=instagram.com|accessdate=November 18, 2015}}</ref><ref name=DaddarioCast>{{cite news|last1=Fleming Jr|first1=Mike|title=Alexandra Daddario Lands \u2018Baywatch\u2019 Female Lead|url=http://deadline.com/2015/11/alexandra-daddario-baywatch-movie-true-detective-dwayne-johnson-zac-efron-1201627862/|accessdate=November 18, 2015|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=November 18, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn January 4, 2016, [[Kelly Rohrbach]]'s casting as C. J. Parker was confirmed by Johnson's [[Instagram]] post.<ref name=Jan2016V>{{cite news|last1=Kroll|first1=Justin|title='Baywatch' Movie Casts Model Kelly Rohrbach in Pamela Anderson's Role|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/baywatch-movie-pamela-anderson-role-kelly-rohrbach-1201645179/|accessdate=January 5, 2016|work=Variety|date=January 4, 2016 }}</ref> Damian Shannon and Mark Swift wrote the screenplay, while the final list of producers were Johnson along with his partner Dany Garcia, through their Seven Bucks Productions, as well as Flynn, Reitman, [[Michael Berk]], [[Douglas Schwartz]], and [[Gregory J. Bonann]].<ref name=\"Jan2016V\" /> On January 20, 2016, Johnson again posted on his Instagram about casting [[Ilfenesh Hadera]] as Johnson's love interest.<ref name=HaderaCast>{{cite news|last1=Evry|first1=Max|title=Ilfenesh Hadera to Play Dwayne Johnson's Love Interest in Baywatch|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/648981-baywatch-movie-adds-ilfenesh-hadera-as-dwayne-johnsons-love-interest|accessdate=January 20, 2016|work=ComingSoon.net|date=January 20, 2016 }}</ref> On January 27, 2016, [[Jon Bass (actor)|Jon Bass]] was cast in the film to play Ronnie, a funny, awkward, and skilled disco dancer at the beach, who falls in love with Parker.<ref name=\"BassCast\">{{cite news|last1=McNary|first1=Dave|title=Dwayne Johnson\u2019s \u2018Baywatch\u2019 Movie Casts Jon Bass|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/baywatch-movie-dwayne-johnson-jon-bass-1201689877/|accessdate=February 3, 2016|work=Variety|date=January 27, 2016}}</ref> On February 12, 2016, [[Hannibal Buress]] joined the cast of the film to play a bay community local.<ref name=\"Feb2016THR\">{{cite news|last1=Kit|first1=Borys|title=Hannibal Buress Joining Dwayne Johnson, Zac Efron in 'Baywatch' (Exclusive)|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hannibal-buress-joining-dwayne-johnson-863599|accessdate=February 15, 2016|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 12, 2016}}</ref> On February 17, 2016, [[Priyanka Chopra]] signed on to star as the antagonist in the film.<ref>{{cite web|title=Priyanka Chopra Officially Joins Dwayne \"The Rock\" Johnson's Baywatch Movie|url=http://www.eonline.com/au/news/730425/is-priyanka-chopra-joining-dwayne-the-rock-johnson-s-baywatch-movie-get-the-scoop|author=Mike, Vulop|work=[[Eonline]]|date=February 17, 2016|accessdate=March 6, 2016}}</ref> The role was originally written for a male. In March 2016, [[Yahya Abdul-Mateen II]] joined the cast as Ellerbee, a police officer who is constantly reminding Mitch that he has no real authority over the bay.<ref>{{cite news|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|title=Yahya Abdul-Mateen II Dives Into \u2018Baywatch\u2019; Jacob Latimore Joins \u2018Collateral Beauty\u2019|url=http://deadline.com/2016/03/yahya-abdul-mateen-ii-baywatch-jacob-latimore-collateral-beauty-1201713044/|accessdate=March 2, 2016|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 2, 2016}}</ref> [[Jack Kesy]] and [[Amin Joseph]] were also cast in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/03/baywatch-movie-jack-kesy-amin-joseph-cast-1201717129/|title=\u2018Baywatch\u2019 Movie: Jack Kesy & Amin Joseph Join Cast|website=Deadline Hollywood|last=Hipes|first=Patrick|date=March 9, 2016}}</ref> [[Vine (service)|Vine]] (later [[YouTube]]) star [[Logan Paul]] announced that he is in the film, but his scenes were later cut.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/LoganPaul/status/705770045184544768|title=Logan Paul on Twitter|work=twitter.com|accessdate=July 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/LoganPaul/status/706080870038429696|title=Logan Paul on Twitter|work=twitter.com|accessdate=July 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://vine.co/v/iXOpLQEnWIW|title=When I asked The Rock if he was ready for our scene in the #BAYWATCH movie \ud83d\ude02|work=vine.co|accessdate=July 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://etcanada.com/news/208178/dwayne-johnson-coaches-social-media-star-logan-paul-on-how-to-bebaywatch/|title=Dwayne Johnson Coaches Social Media Star Logan Paul On How To #BeBaywatch|last=West|first=Rachel|date=February 28, 2017|work=ET Canada|access-date=March 2, 2017}}</ref>  [[Izabel Goulart]] also appeared.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gq.globo.com/Cultura/Cinema/noticia/2016/03/top-izabel-goulart-da-pistas-de-participacao-em-novo-baywatch.html|title=Top Izabel Goulart d\u00e1 pistas de participa\u00e7\u00e3o em novo 'Baywatch'|work=GQ|last=|first=|date=March 15, 2016}}</ref> NFL players [[Vernon Davis]] and [[Arian Foster]] also have cameo appearances in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://247sports.com/nfl/washington-redskins/Bolt/Vernon-Davis-worked-with-The-Rock-in-Baywatch-in-cameo-role-52959039|title=Vernon Davis Washington Redskins worked with The Rock in 'Baywatch' in cameo role|author=|date=|website=247sports.com|accessdate=January 8, 2018}}{{Dead link|date=August 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/the-baywatch-cameos-honor-david-hasselhoff-pamela-anderson-a-superstar-gymnast-59537|title=The 'Baywatch' Cameos Honor David Hasselhoff, Pamela Anderson, & A Superstar Gymnast|first=Olivia|last=Truffaut-Wong|date=|website=bustle.com|accessdate=January 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\n[[Principal photography]] on the film began on February 22, 2016, in [[Deerfield Beach, Florida]], with the setting in [[Broward County, Florida|Broward County]], Florida, while the TV series was set in [[Malibu, California]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Ripped and ready to go! The Rock and Zac Efron start lifeguard duty as cameras start rolling on Baywatch movie in Florida|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-3459221/Ripped-ready-Rock-Zac-Efron-start-lifeguard-duty-cameras-start-rolling-Baywatch-movie-Florida.html|accessdate=February 23, 2016|work=Daily Mail|date=February 22, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Shooting on the Baywatch movie has begun|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/02/22/baywatch-movie-begins|accessdate=February 23, 2016|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=February 22, 2016}}</ref> The film was shot in [[Miami]] and [[Savannah, Georgia]].<ref name=\"Feb2016THR\" /><ref>{{cite news|title=\u2018Baywatch\u2019 begins filming next week; Open casting call for extras announced|url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2016/02/16/baywatch-begins-filming-next-week-open-casting-call-extras-announced/#lightbox-gallery-pv6p/0/|accessdate=February 21, 2016|work=OLV|date=February 16, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='Baywatch' Movie Open Casting Call for Kid and Teen Actors|url=http://www.projectcasting.com/casting-calls-acting-auditions/baywatch-movie-open-casting-call-for-kid-and-teen-actors|accessdate=February 15, 2016|work=Project Casting|date=January 28, 2016}}</ref> In late March 2016, filming started in [[Tybee Island, Georgia|Tybee Island]], Georgia.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dwayne Johnson continues filming 'Baywatch' in Tybee Island, Georgia|url=http://www.onlocationvacations.com/2016/03/30/dwayne-johnson-zac-efron-continue-baywatch-filming-tybee-island-georgia/|accessdate=April 2, 2016|work=On Location Vacations|issue=March 30, 2016}}</ref> Filming wrapped on May 18, 2016.<ref name=2017FFS>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=August 2018|title=2017 Feature Film Study|url=https://www.filmla.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/2017_film_study_v3-WEB.pdf|publisher=FilmL.A. |page=Page 24|accessdate=August 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nIn January 2016, [[Paramount Pictures]] scheduled ''Baywatch'' for a May 19, 2017 release, which was originally scheduled for a sequel to ''[[Terminator Genisys]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Verhoeven|first1=Beatrice|title='Terminator 2' Pulled From Schedule, 'Baywatch' Release Date Set|url=https://www.thewrap.com/baywatch-release-date-set-terminator-2-pulled-from-schedule/|accessdate=January 21, 2016|work=TheWrap|date=January 20, 2016 }}</ref> In December 2016, Paramount pushed the release date back one week to May 26, 2017, to avoid competition with ''[[Alien: Covenant]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=D'Alessandro|first1=Anthony|title=\u2018Baywatch\u2019 Surfs To Memorial Day Weekend, \u2018Life\u2019 Flies To March|url=http://deadline.com/2016/12/baywatch-dwayne-johnson-memorial-day-weekend-1201864965/|accessdate=December 5, 2016|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=December 5, 2016 }}</ref> In April 2017, the film was moved one day earlier, to avoid direct competition with ''[[Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/baywatch-paramount-may-release-date-1202064755/ |title=\u2018Baywatch\u2019 Looking To Catch A Wave At The B.O. By Opening One Day Earlier |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=April 7, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n''Baywatch'' grossed $58.1 million in the United States and Canada and $119.8 million in other territories, for a worldwide total of $177.8 million, against a production budget of $69 million.<ref name=BOM />\n\nIn the United States and Canada, the film was initially projected to gross around $40 million from 3,642 theaters over its five-day opening weekend, with the studio predicting a more conservative $30 million debut.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/05/pirates-of-the-caribbean-dead-men-tell-no-tales-johnny-depp-memorial-day-box-office-opening-1202084122/|title=\u2018Pirates Of The Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales\u2019 To Breathe Life Back Into Memorial Day B.O. With Est. $100M Debut|author= Anthony D'Alessandro|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=May 4, 2017|accessdate=May 7, 2017}}</ref><ref name=preview>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-preview-pirates-5-baywatch-set-sail-uncertain-shores-1007067 |title=Box-Office Preview: 'Pirates 5,' 'Baywatch' Set Sail for Uncertain Shores |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=May 24, 2017}}</ref> It made $1.25 million at 2,554 theaters from Wednesday night previews, similar to fellow mid-week R-rated releases ''[[We're the Millers]]'' ($1.7 million) and ''[[Let's Be Cops]]'' ($1.2 million).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/05/baywatch-wednesday-preview-box-office-opening-1202102337/|title=\u2018Baywatch\u2019 Swims To $1.25M In Wednesday Night Previews|author= Anthony D'Alessandro |work=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 25, 2017}}</ref> However, after making $4.6 million on its opening day (including Wednesday night previews) and $5.7 million on Friday, five-day projections were lowered to $25 million. It ended up grossing $18.5 million in its opening weekend (for a five-day total of $27.7 million), finishing third at the box office, behind ''[[Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales]]'' ($63 million) and ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2]]'' ($20.9 million).<ref name=\"opening\">{{cite magazine|url=http://deadline.com/2017/05/pirates-of-the-caribbean-5-dead-men-tell-no-tales-baywatch-box-office-weekend-1202102887/|title=How \u2018Pirates\u2019 & \u2018Baywatch\u2019 Are Casualties Of Summer Franchise Fatigue At The Domestic B.O.|magazine=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]|accessdate=May 28, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2017/05/28/baywatch-bombs-at-box-office-pirates-caribbean-wins-memorial-day-weekend.html|title='Baywatch' bombs at box office, 'Pirates of the Caribbean' wins Memorial Day weekend|date=May 28, 2017|work=Fox News|access-date=May 28, 2017 }}</ref> In its second weekend the film grossed $8.8 million (a drop of 52.5%), finishing 5th at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2017/06/04/box-office-pirates-5-sails-past-500m-worldwide-baywatch-and-alien-crumble/?s=BoxOffice|title=Box Office: 'Pirates 5' Sails Past $500M Worldwide, 'Baywatch' And 'Alien' Crumble|author=Scott Mendelson|author-link= Scott Mendelson |work=Forbes|date=June 4, 2017|accessdate=June 4, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\nOn review aggregation website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film has an approval rating of 18% based on 234 reviews, and an average rating of 4/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''Baywatch'' takes its source material's [[Jiggle television|jiggle factor]] to R-rated levels, but lacks the original's campy charm \u2013 and leaves its charming stars flailing in the shallows.\"<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/baywatch_2017 |title=Baywatch (2017) |publisher= [[Fandango Media]] |work= [[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate= May 14, 2018 }}</ref> On [[Metacritic]] the film has a weighted average score of 37 out of 100, based on 47 critics, indicating \"generally unfavorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.metacritic.com/movie/baywatch |title= Baywatch Reviews |publisher= [[CBS Interactive]] |work= [[Metacritic]] |date= June 10, 2017 }}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"B+\" on an A+ to F scale, while [[PostTrak]] reported filmgoers gave it a 76% overall positive score.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/06/wonder-woman-beats-tom-cruise-mummy-at-the-box-office-1202110164/ |title=Why \u2018The Mummy\u2019 Turned Crummy At The Domestic B.O. & What This Means For Uni\u2019s \u2018Dark Universe\u2019|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=June 10, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"opening\" /> Dwayne Johnson responded to critics' reviews, saying that the film was made for fans and that they loved it.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.vulture.com/2017/05/dont-blame-critics-for-blockbusters-bad-box-office.html |title= Don\u2019t Blame Critics When Your Blockbusters Are Bad |last= Buchanan |first= Kyle |work= [[Vulture.com]] |date= May 31, 2017 |accessdate= August 2, 2017 }}</ref><ref name=\"thr-roundup\" />\n\nWriting for ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', [[Peter Travers]] praised the \"easy rapport\" of Johnson and Efron while saying, \"what [the film] needs more is a functional script\". Travers rated it two out of four stars and said, \"Think of yourself sitting down for a big two-hour wallow in instant stupid with a vat of popcorn, slathered in fake butter and possibly a mound of melted M&Ms on top. It feels great chugging it down, then your stomach hurts, your head aches and you puke the whole thing up so you can forget about it in the morning. That's ''Baywatch'' in a nutshell.\"<ref>{{cite web |title='Baywatch' Review: Bring on the Beach Bods, Boobs and Bodily Fluids |last= Travers |first= Peter |date= May 23, 2017 |work= [[Rolling Stone]] |url= https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/reviews/peter-travers-baywatch-has-the-beach-bods-bodily-fluids-w483930 |accessdate= May 27, 2017}}</ref> Owen Gleiberman of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' called it \"stupidly entertaining... for a while\" but was critical of the plot.<ref>{{cite web |date= 23 May 2017|last= Gleiberman |first= Owen |author-link= Owen Gleiberman|title=Film Review: \u2018Baywatch\u2019 |url= https://variety.com/2017/film/reviews/baywatch-review-dwayne-johnson-zac-efron-1202428442/ |website=Variety }}</ref> Brian Truitt  of ''[[USA Today]]'' gave the film two out of four stars, and said that while the film has all the elements you would expect \"the remake yearns to be both sendup farce and straight action film, tripping along the way and failing to grasp either.\"<ref>{{cite web |date= |last= Truitt |first= Brian |title= Review: Dwayne Johnson's bland 'Baywatch' can't commit to the absurd |url= https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2017/05/23/review-baywatch-movie-dwayne-johnson-zac-efron/102011794/ |website= USA TODAY }}</ref> [[Richard Roeper]] of the ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' gave the film 1.5 out of 4 stars, writing: \"As was the case with ''[[CHiPs (film)|CHiPS]]'', ''[[The Dukes of Hazzard (film)|The Dukes of Hazzard]]'', ''[[The Beverly Hillbillies (film)|The Beverly Hillbillies]]'', ''[[Car 54, Where Are You? (film)|Car 54, Where Are You?]]'' and I'll just stop there, when you make films from junk TV, more often than not you're going to wind up with a junk movie.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Baywatch\u2019: A dumb TV show inspires a dumb movie |date= May 24, 2017 |last= Roeper |first= Richard |author-link= Richard Roeper |work= [[Chicago Sun-Times]] |url= http://chicago.suntimes.com/entertainment/smartly-there-latest-pirates-of-the-caribbean-picks-up-the-pace/ }}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\n''Baywatch'' was released on [[Digital distribution|Digital HD]] on August 15, 2017<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bradley|first1=Dan|title=\u2018Baywatch\u2019 4K Unrated, Blu-ray, DVD and Digital Release Date, Details and Artwork|url=http://www.thehdroom.com/bluray/baywatch-4k-unrated-blu-ray-dvd-digital-release-date-details-artwork-110129/|website=HD Room|accessdate=July 29, 2017}}</ref> and on [[Blu-ray]] and [[DVD]] on August 29, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Baywatch (2017)|url=http://www.dvdsreleasedates.com/movies/7670/baywatch|website=DVDs Release Dates|accessdate=August 2, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width: 99%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Recipient(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"| 2017\n| rowspan=\"5\"| [[2017 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Actor \u2013 Comedy|Choice Movie: Comedy Actor]]\n| [[Dwayne Johnson]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"5\"| <ref name=\"variety-teenchoice-winners\">{{cite web |last1=Knapp |first1=JD |last2=Rubin |first2=Rebecca |title=Teen Choice Awards 2017: \u2018Riverdale,\u2019 Fifth Harmony Shut Out Competition |url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/awards/teen-choice-awards-2017-tcas-fox-winners-list-riverdale-fifth-harmony-1202526197/ |website=Variety |accessdate=August 14, 2017 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170814094055/http://variety.com/2017/tv/awards/teen-choice-awards-2017-tcas-fox-winners-list-riverdale-fifth-harmony-1202526197/ |archive-date=August 14, 2017 |date=August 14, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Zac Efron]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Cho