{"title_page": "Novaya Adygea", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Novaya Adygea\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0410\u0434\u044b\u0433\u0435\u044f \n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Settlement\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Adygea#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Adygea]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Takhtamukaysky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|45|01|N|38|55|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/adigeya/tahtamukayskiy-rayon/aul-novaya-adigeya/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0430\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0410\u0434\u044b\u0433\u0435\u044f \u0432 \u0440\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0435 \u0410\u0434\u044b\u0433\u0435\u044f]</ref>\n}}\n'''Novaya Adygea''' ({{lang-ru|\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0410\u0434\u044b\u0433\u0435\u044f}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a settlement) in Starobzhegokayskoye Rural Settlement of [[Takhtamukaysky District]], the [[Adygea|Republic of Adygea]], [[Russia]]. The population was 3816 as of 2018.<ref>[http://krsdstat.gks.ru/wps/wcm/connect/rosstat_ts/krsdstat/resources/3ca4e38044dfe71585cbafde4cdebdf4/%D0%A7%D0%B8%D1%81%D0%BB%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BD%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D1%8C+%D0%BF%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%8F%D0%BD%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B3%D0%BE+%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%81%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%8F+%D0%BF%D0%BE+%D0%9C%D0%9E+%D0%B8+%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%81%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BD%D1%8B%D0%BC+%D0%BF%D1%83%D0%BD%D0%BA%D1%82%D0%B0%D0%BC+%D0%A0%D0%B5%D1%81%D0%BF%D1%83%D0%B1%D0%BB%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%B8+%D0%90%D0%B4%D1%8B%D0%B3%D0%B5%D1%8F+%D0%BF%D0%BE+%D1%81%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%8F%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%8E+%D0%BD%D0%B0+1+%D1%8F%D0%BD%D0%B2%D0%B0%D1%80%D1%8F+2018+%D0%B3%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%B0.doc \u0427\u0438\u0441\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u043e \u041c\u041e \u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043f\u0443\u043d\u043a\u0442\u0430\u043c \u0420\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u0410\u0434\u044b\u0433\u0435\u044f \u043f\u043e \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u043d\u0438\u044e \u043d\u0430 1 \u044f\u043d\u0432\u0430\u0440\u044f 2018 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430]</ref> There are 43 streets.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Takhtamukaysky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Adygea]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Takhtamukaysky District]]\n\n{{Adygea-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Novaya Adygea\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0410\u0434\u044b\u0433\u0435\u044f \n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Settlement\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Adygea#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Adygea]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Takhtamukaysky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|45|01|N|38|55|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/adigeya/tahtamukayskiy-rayon/aul-novaya-adigeya/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0430\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0410\u0434\u044b\u0433\u0435\u044f \u0432 \u0440\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0435 \u0410\u0434\u044b\u0433\u0435\u044f]</ref>\n}}\n'''Novaya Adygea''' ({{lang-ru|\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u0410\u0434\u044b\u0433\u0435\u044f}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a settlement) in Starobzhegokayskoye Rural Settlement of [[Takhtamukaysky District]], the [[Adygea|Republic of Adygea]], [[Russia]]. The population was 3816 as of 2018.<ref>[http://krsdstat.gks.ru/wps/wcm/connect/rosstat_ts/krsdstat/resources/3ca4e38044dfe71585cbafde4cdebdf4/%D0%A7%D0%B8%D1%81%D0%BB%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BD%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D1%8C+%D0%BF%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%8F%D0%BD%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B3%D0%BE+%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%81%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%8F+%D0%BF%D0%BE+%D0%9C%D0%9E+%D0%B8+%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%81%D0%B5%D0%BB%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BD%D1%8B%D0%BC+%D0%BF%D1%83%D0%BD%D0%BA%D1%82%D0%B0%D0%BC+%D0%A0%D0%B5%D1%81%D0%BF%D1%83%D0%B1%D0%BB%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%B8+%D0%90%D0%B4%D1%8B%D0%B3%D0%B5%D1%8F+%D0%BF%D0%BE+%D1%81%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%8F%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%8E+%D0%BD%D0%B0+1+%D1%8F%D0%BD%D0%B2%D0%B0%D1%80%D1%8F+2018+%D0%B3%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%B0.doc \u0427\u0438\u0441\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043f\u043e \u041c\u041e \u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043f\u0443\u043d\u043a\u0442\u0430\u043c \u0420\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u0410\u0434\u044b\u0433\u0435\u044f \u043f\u043e \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u043d\u0438\u044e \u043d\u0430 1 \u044f\u043d\u0432\u0430\u0440\u044f 2018 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430]</ref> There are 43 streets.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Takhtamukaysky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Adygea]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Takhtamukaysky District]]\n\n\n{{Adygea-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Wagino 20100516", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:typos", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novaya_Adygea"}
{"title_page": "Dead Space (video game)", "text_new": "{{short description|Video game}}\n{{for|the mobile game|Dead Space (mobile game)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title      = Dead Space\n| image      = Dead Space Box Art.jpg\n| developer  = [[EA Redwood Shores]]\n| publisher  = [[Electronic Arts]]\n| director   = [[Michael Condrey]]<br/>[[Bret Robbins]]\n| producer   = {{Unbulleted list|[[Glen Schofield]]|Chuck Beaver|Steve Papoutsis}}\n| designer   = \n| programmer = Steve Timson\n| artist     = Ian Milham\n| writer     = [[Warren Ellis]]<br/>[[Rick Remender]]<br/>[[Antony Johnston]]\n| composer   = [[Jason Graves]]\n| series     = ''[[Dead Space (series)|Dead Space]]''\n| engine     = \n| platforms  = [[PlayStation 3]]<br/>[[Xbox 360]]<br/>[[Microsoft Windows]]\n| released   = {{Video game release|NA|October 13, 2008<ref name=\"releasedate\">{{cite web|title=EA Announces That Dead Space Has Gone Gold |date=September 4, 2008 |url=http://info.ea.com/release.asp?i=986 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20121216082707/http://info.ea.com/release.asp?i=986 |url-status=dead |archive-date=December 16, 2012 |accessdate=October 26, 2008 }}</ref>|NA|October 20, 2008 (PC)<ref name=\"releasedate\"/>|AU|October 23, 2008<ref name=\"releasedate\"/>|EU|October 24, 2008<ref name=\"releasedate\"/>}}\n| genre      = [[Survival horror]]\n| modes      = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]]\n}}\n\n'''''Dead Space''''' is a science fiction [[survival horror]] [[video game]], developed by [[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]] (Subsequently known as [[Visceral Games]]) for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 3]] and [[Xbox 360]]. The game was released in October 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://store.steampowered.com/app/17470/|title=Dead Space on Steam|publisher=Steam|accessdate=December 10, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100514121759/http://store.steampowered.com/app/17470|archive-date=May 14, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref> The game has a strong science fiction atmosphere and is set in a [[spacecraft]]. It puts the player in control of an [[engineer]] named Isaac Clarke who fights the Necromorphs, the monstrous reanimated human corpses aboard an interstellar mining ship, the ''USG Ishimura''.<ref name=ignpreview1>{{cite web|last=Wales|first=Matt|title=Dead Space Preview|publisher=IGN|url=http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/850/850346p1.html|accessdate=May 19, 2008|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/68DDLpplN?url=http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/850/850346p1.html|archive-date=June 6, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n''Dead Space'' was met with widespread critical acclaim, being cited as one of the [[greatest video games of all time]] and sold over 2 million copies. The sequels, ''[[Dead Space 2]]'' and ''[[Dead Space 3]]'' were released on January 25, 2011<ref>{{cite video game|title=[[Dead Space 2]]|developer=[[Visceral Games]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=January 25, 2011|platform=[[personal computer|PC]] (Microsoft Windows), [[PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox 360]]|version=|level=|quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=IGN|work=Voodoo Extreme|title=Dead Space 2 Release Date Confirmed \u2013 January 25, 2011|date=June 14, 2010|url=http://ve3d.ign.com/articles/news/55363/Dead-Space-2-Release-Date-Confirmed-January-25-2011|accessdate=January 21, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101003092925/http://ve3d.ign.com/articles/news/55363/Dead-Space-2-Release-Date-Confirmed-January-25-2011|archive-date=October 3, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref> and February 5, 2013 respectively.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|title=Dead Space 3 Hits Shelves \u2013 February 5, 2013|date=February 5, 2013|url=http://www.ea.com/news/dead-space-3-hits-shelves|accessdate=February 5, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130208131748/http://www.ea.com/news/dead-space-3-hits-shelves|archive-date=February 8, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Gameplay==\n[[File:Deadspace1.jpg|thumb|left|Isaac fighting a group of Necromorphs.]]\nThe player controls Isaac Clarke, a ship systems engineer who must fight his way through a mining starship infested with an alien scourge. The crew was horrifically slaughtered and their corpses are reanimated into creatures known as \"Necromorphs\". The various types of Necromorphs appeared throughout the game, each with different abilities and requiring different tactics to defeat. The game is played from an over-the-shoulder third-person perspective.<ref name=ignpreview1 />\n\n''Dead Space'' does not use a traditional [[HUD (video gaming)|heads-up display]]. Instead, all information is relayed to the player via [[Holography|holographic projections]] from Isaac's Resource Integration Gear (RIG) spacesuit and the weapons themselves. For example, a small holographic display is mounted on Isaac's weapons to indicate the ammunition count while aiming. Also, the health meter is integrated into his suit spine and the spines of the suits that are worn by the other game characters.<ref name=gamespypreview1>{{cite web|last=Graziani|first=Gabe|title=Previews: Dead Space|work=GameSpy.com|publisher=IGN Entertainment|date=October 9, 2007|url=http://uk.xbox360.gamespy.com/xbox-360/dead-space/825786p1.html|accessdate=May 20, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080214075024/http://uk.xbox360.gamespy.com/xbox-360/dead-space/825786p1.html|archive-date=February 14, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref> The player can check the current objectives and the 3D map via the floating holograms that are projected in front of Isaac or access the inventory screen to manage items or choose guns. However, the game still progresses in real-time during these activities so the player remains in danger of being attacked while browsing through menus and the map.<ref name=gamespypreview1 />\n\nCombat involves a mechanism called \"strategic [[dismemberment]]\" which the player must cut the limbs or sections of the individual Necromorphs off to defeat them. For example, shooting most Necromorphs in the head will have little effect and will only disorient them. However, they can be stopped once the player removes it's arms and legs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadspaceinformationsite.weebly.com/necromorphs.html |title=Necromorphs Dismemberment |date=January 16, 2015 |access-date=January 16, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121213704/http://deadspaceinformationsite.weebly.com/necromorphs.html |archive-date=January 21, 2016 |url-status=live  }}</ref> Depending on how they are wounded, the Necromorphs can adopt new stances and tactics such as sprouting new limbs or giving birth to new enemies in the process.<ref name=ignhandson>{{cite web|last=Haynes|first=Jeff|title=Dead Space Hands-on|work=IGN.com|publisher=IGN Entertainment|date=May 17, 2008|url=http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/874/874895p1.html|accessdate=May 20, 2008|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/68DDP7ZXO?url=http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/874/874895p1.html|archive-date=June 6, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn keeping with Isaac's profession as an engineer, the weapons in ''Dead Space'' are mostly improvised from the mining tools<ref name=gamespypreview1 /> such as a Plasma Cutter (For horizontal and vertical slicing), [[rotary saw]], a [[hydrazine]] torch (Repurposed as a [[flamethrower]]), a high-energy demolition beam and a cannon that emits powerful [[shock wave]]s. A military-grade [[automatic rifle]] is available and Isaac can also attack the enemies by clubbing them with his weapon or stomping on them. All weapons featured a secondary-fire mode. For example, the Plasma Cutter can be rotated 90 degrees for more effective dismemberment of vertical limbs (Such as legs on a normal [[Bipedalism|bipedal]] humanoid).<ref>{{cite web|first=Jeff|last=Haynes|url=http://uk.ps3.ign.com/articles/908/908187p1.html|title=Weapons of Dead Space|publisher=IGN|date=September 5, 2008|accessdate=December 18, 2011}}</ref> The player must scavenge for ammunition and items which are found throughout the ship or dropped by the Necromorphs when they are killed. The automated Stores throughout the ship can be accessed to buy and sell items or store them for later use. The player can use [[workbench]]es to upgrade Isaac's suit and weapons.\n\nOther than weapons, Isaac is equipped with other tools to help him survive, solve puzzles and combat the enemies more effectively. Isaac's Stasis ability can be used to slow the enemies and objects down temporarily and a Kinesis module allows Isaac to move and throw the items sufficiently. The heavy or sharp objects can become improvised projectile weapons.<ref name=gamespypreview1 /> ''Dead Space'' features [[Weightlessness|zero gravity]] environments, through which Isaac can navigate by using magnetic boots.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Anderson|first1=Lark|title=Dead Space Review|url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/dead-space-review/1900-6200447/|website=[[GameSpot]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|date=October 31, 2014|accessdate=July 14, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331135937/http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/dead-space-review/1900-6200447/|archive-date=March 31, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Isaac's suit will protect him from the direct effects of [[vacuum]] or toxic environments, but it has a limited air supply and he will eventually [[Asphyxia|suffocate]] so the player is forced to proceed quickly when in these situations.\n\n==Plot==\nThe story is set in the year, 2508 and begins when the USG {{nihongo|''Ishimura''|\u77f3\u6751||\"Stone Village\"}}, a \"planet-cracker\" [[starship]], designed to extract the ore in large masses of billions of tons sent a [[distress signal]] out to the Concordance Extraction Corporation (CEC) during a [[Asteroid mining|mining]] operation on the planet called Aegis VII. The CEC dispatches the USG ''Kellion'' to investigate. After a guidance system malfunction crashes the ''Kellion'' into the ''Ishimura'' dock, the crew tries to seek other means of transport.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Dead Space|developer=[[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=October 14, 2008|platform=[[Microsoft Windows]]/[[PlayStation 3]]/[[Xbox 360]]|version=|scene=|level=Chapter 1|language=|isolang=|quote=}}</ref> As they explored what appears to be an abandoned ship, they are attacked by grotesque monsters, killing all, but a ship systems engineer named Isaac Clarke, Commander Zach Hammond and a computer specialist named Kendra Daniels. Hammond notices that many of the ship's systems are failing. He and Daniels directed and assisted Isaac in fixing them to keep them alive for rescue.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Dead Space|developer=[[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=October 14, 2008|platform=[[Microsoft Windows]]/[[PlayStation 3]]/[[Xbox 360]]|version=|scene=Go To Medical (video log)level=Chapter 1|language=|isolang=|quote='''Hammond''': ''[after the'' Kellion ''explodes and Isaac fights off several Necromorphs]'' What the hell is happening down there?! What happened to the shuttle? / '''Kendra''': That was our ride home. It's the only way off this ship... / '''Hammond''': Kendra\u2026 / '''Kendra''': No, Hammond! This changes ''everything!'' / '''Hammond''': Just let me think! ''[pause]'' Can you access the Command Computer? / '''Kendra''': It's no good. There's an executive lockdown of all primary systems. Without the Captain's authorization, I ''can't'' access them. / '''Hammond''': Well? Where's the Captain? / '''Kendra''': ''[using the computer terminal]'' Here he is. Captain Benjamin Matthius. Location...Medlab. Status...Deceased. / '''Hammond''': What? How? / '''Kendra''': I can't access that information. Find the Captain and you'll find his RIG. With his authorization codes, I can crack this computer wide open. / ''[There is the sound of something moving around in a ventilation shaft above them.]'' / '''Hammond''': Dammit! Isaac, I'm sending the Tram back to your location. Get to the Medical Deck and find that RIG as fast as you can!}}</ref><ref name=\"Dead Space\">{{cite video game|title=Dead Space|developer=[[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=October 14, 2008|platform=[[Microsoft Windows]]/[[PlayStation 3]]/[[Xbox 360]]|version=|scene=|level=|language=|isolang=|quote=}}</ref>\n\nAs Isaac moves about making the necessary repairs, he discovers the various text and audio logs that are scattered throughout the ship by piecing the events together that transpired prior to his arrival: During the course of it's illegal mining of Aegis VII, the ''Ishimura's'' crew found the Red Marker, the most valuable relic of Unitology, an influential and powerful religion. A covert group of devout Unitologists led by Captain Benjamin Mathius had themselves transferred aboard the ''Ishimura'' in a mission to bring the Marker to Earth.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Dead Space|developer=[[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=October 14, 2008|platform=[[Microsoft Windows]]/[[PlayStation 3]]/[[Xbox 360]]|version=|scene=Engine Problems (video log)|level=Chapter 2|language=|isolang=|quote='''Hammond''': Isaac! Somehow, one of them [Necromorphs] found a way down to the captain's nest! I managed to contain it in a damaged escape pod. \u2026Lifting the executive lockdown. I found the deck logs. Whatever is happening around here, it came from the planet when they cracked it open. It spread to the colony and reached the ship. Isaac, this isn't an infection; it's some form of alien life! ''[static]'' Shit! We've got bigger problems. The ship's engines are offline and out orbit is decaying! Get over to the Engineering deck ASAP, while I stay here and figure out what the problem is.}}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|title=Dead Space|developer=[[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=October 14, 2008|platform=[[Microsoft Windows]]/[[PlayStation 3]]/[[Xbox 360]]|version=|scene=|level=Chapter 8|language=|isolang=|quote=}}</ref> Soon after the Marker's extraction to the ''Ishimura'', the humans from the planet's colony and the ship suffered from [[mass hysteria]], violent [[hallucinations]] and homicidal dementia before subsequently killing each other. Dr. Terrence Kyne, the ship's chief science officer and a Unitologist grew disillusioned with his religion after witnessing the horrifying effects that the Marker had on others and began to feel at odds with the other Unitologists on board.\n\nMathius eventually cutted the traffic and communications off between the two sides by going insane. Dr. Kyne tried to relieve Mathius of duty only to accidentally kill the Captain in a struggle.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Dead Space|developer=[[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=October 14, 2008|platform=[[Microsoft Windows]]/[[PlayStation 3]]/[[Xbox 360]]|version=|scene=Captain's Demise (video log)|level=Chapter 4|language=|isolang=|quote=''[Kyne stands in front of Matthius; two bridge staff stand behind him.]'' '''Matthius''': ''[looking behind him, at the two bridge staff]'' This is mutiny. You'll all be tried for mutiny! Kyne, make them listen to reason. / '''Kyne''': Settle down, now. ''[to the bridge staff]'' Hold him. ''[The two men restrain Matthius from behind by the arms.]'' By Maritime Law Article 54\u201369, I hereby declare Captain Benjamin Matthius unfit for duty.'''Matthius''': The Marker...must be delivered to the church! Terrence! ''Please!'' / '''Kyne''': ''[turns away, and readies a needle]'' I'm sorry, Ben. But I can't let you do this. / '''Matthius''': ''[angered]'' Traitor. Heretic!'''Kyne''': ''[turns back around]'' Hold his head. / '''Matthius''': ''Murderer!'' / '''Kyne''': Hold him! / ''[Matthius begins to violently struggle in the men's grasp. Kyne tries to get a clean shot with the needle, trying to inject it in his neck. However, the needle goes right into Matthius' left eye. Matthius screams in agony, blood pouring out of his eye socket. The two men let go of him in shock, and Matthius falls backward onto the flood, dead.]'' '''Bridge Staff 1''': He's...dead! / '''Kyne''': N-No, it was an accident! I had to stop him! / '''Bridge staff 2:''' Arrest the doctor.}}</ref> An alien virus, the genetic coding which is encrypted on the Marker began ravaging the Aegis VII colony, infecting any available corpses and turning them into \"Necromorphs\" \u2013 mutated and reanimated corpses that violently slaughtered the uninfected humans to spread the infestation.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Dead Space|developer=[[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=October 14, 2008|platform=[[PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox 360]]|version=|scene=Report from Kendra (audio log)|level=Chapter 4|language=|isolang=|quote='''Kendra''': Isaac, listen up. I've gone over the medical reports. These things are BIO-RECOMBINATORS. They take dead tissue, absorb it and molds it into new forms. One iteration seems to have the sole purpose of infecting corpses; the others\u2026well, seem to be making corpses to infect. And that body tissue we keep seeing on the walls is part of it, too. I found a report that says it's a habitat changer.}}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|title=Dead Space|developer=[[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=October 14, 2008|platform=[[PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox 360]]|version=|scene=Mercer's Journal (audio log)|level=Chapter 2|language=|isolang=|quote='''Mercer''': I finally convinced Jurgens to show me the video feed from the colony. And what I saw was glorious. Breathtaking. Miners undergoing a transformation into something extraordinary. I must know more. Even as the believer within me wants to become one of them, the scientist needs to uncover their secrets. I need to study one of these... Necromorphs, as Kyne so clinically puts it. I need to witness this infection first hand. Perhaps that patient from the colony...}}</ref> A colony shuttle that was carrying an infectious Necromorph caused the scourge to spread across the ''Ishimura''. Though Hammond states that he is unaware about what the Marker is, Daniels confides to Isaac that Hammond may be lying. Isaac encounters his girlfriend, Nicole Brennan, a medical officer aboard the ''Ishimura'' though they are unable to meet.<ref name=\"Dead Space\"/>\n\nAfter repairing the critical systems, Isaac's team launches the second beacon, attracting the nearby military vessel called the USM ''Valor''. However, the ''Valor'', having picked an escape pod with a Necromorph inside up that was jettisoned earlier by Hammond is overrun and crashes into the ship. Hammond deduces from the military equipment that he finds on board that the ''Valor'' was actually assigned to destroy the ''Ishimura'', later confirmed through a text log found on the ''Valor''.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Dead Space|developer=[[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=October 14, 2008|platform=[[PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox 360]]|version=|scene=|level=Chapter 10|language=|isolang=|quote='''Hammond (holo-link)''': I just read through the ''Valor''s munition logs. Their presence here can't be a coincidence. ''[\u2026]'' They were on a search-and-destroy mission, do you hear me?!}}</ref> Deciding that they must escape while they can, Isaac and Hammond retrieved the ''Valor''{{'}}s singularity core in order to repair an available shuttle though Hammond is killed by an enhanced Necromorph in the process. Dr. Kyne who was one of the last survivors of the ''Ishimura'' contacted Isaac by urging him to return the Marker to Aegis VII, believing that it can restrain the \"[[Group mind (science fiction)|Hive Mind]]\", a creature that controls the Necromorphs.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Dead Space|developer=[[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=October 14, 2008|platform=[[PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox 360]]|version=|scene=|level=Chapter 9|language=|isolang=|quote='''Hammond (holo-link)''': Isaac? Isaac, are you there? ''[\u2026]'' / '''Kendra (holo-link)''': Hammond?! Where the hell have you been? / '''Hammond (holo-link)''': Surviving. Barely. ''[...]'' Listen up: I'm calling abort on the mission. Fuck the CEC crew and fuck the chain of command. We've gotta get the hell out of here.}}</ref> After assisting Isaac in loading the Marker onto the shuttle, Daniels murders Kyne and betrays Isaac, revealing herself as a government operative ordered to retrieve the Marker for her superiors.<ref name=\"Dead Space\"/> She reveals that the Marker is a [[Reverse engineering|reverse-engineered]] copy of the Black Marker that was found on Earth and placed on Aegis VII by the government to monitor it's effects. She leaves on the shuttle without Isaac, but Nicole arrives and helps him recall the shuttle via remote pilot, prompting Daniels to flee via escape pod.<ref name=\"Dead Space\"/>\n\nIsaac takes the Marker back to the colony, pacifying the Hive Mind and creating a \"dead space\" that makes all Necromorphs in the surrounding area dormant. However, this also disrupts the [[Artificial gravity (fiction)|gravity tethers]] that are keeping Aegis VII from tearing itself apart.<ref name=\"Dead Space\"/> Before Isaac can leave, Daniels appears and starts to take the Marker back to the shuttle. She shows Isaac through a recovered distress transmission that Nicole committed suicide via lethal injection before Isaac's team arrived on the ''Ishimura''. His [[Hallucination|vision]]s of her were the Marker's attempts to bring itself back to the planet.<ref name=\"RedwoodShores\">{{cite video game|title=Dead Space|developer=[[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=October 14, 2008|platform=[[PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox 360]]|version=|scene=|level=Chapter 13|language=|isolang=|quote=}}</ref> Isaac intercepts Daniels loading the Marker back into the shuttle. Before she can leave, the Hive Mind reawakens, violently killing her, leaving Isaac to defeat it in a ferocious battle.<ref name=\"RedwoodShores\" />\n\nLeaving the Marker behind, Isaac flies off in the shuttle before the colony and the Marker are destroyed. As he sets a course away from Aegis VII, Isaac removes his helmet and watches Nicole's first transmission again. Now knowing how it ends, he turns it off before it can finish. Noticing something in his peripherals, Isaac looks to his right and is attacked by a vision of a bloody Nicole just before the scene cuts to black.<ref>{{cite video game|title=Dead Space|developer=[[Visceral Games|EA Redwood Shores]]|publisher=[[Electronic Arts]]|date=October 14, 2008|platform=[[PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox 360]]|version=|scene=Ending|level=|language=|isolang=|quote=}}</ref>\n\n==Development==\n[[Electronic Arts]] announced ''Dead Space'' in September 2007.<ref>{{cite web|title=EA Announce Dead Space|url=http://www.xbox360achievements.org/news/news-153-EA-Announce-Dead-Space.html|publisher=EA|accessdate=July 26, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090909112201/http://www.xbox360achievements.org/news/news-153-EA-Announce-Dead-Space.html|archive-date=September 9, 2009|url-status=live}}</ref> The game was developed at their studio in [[Redwood Shores, California]]. A 2006 rumor suggested that the studio was working on a ''[[System Shock]]'' sequel.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.g4tv.com/thefeed/blog/post/713030/the-lost-history-of-system-shock |title=Archived copy |access-date=November 28, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130113082649/http://www.g4tv.com/thefeed/blog/post/713030/the-lost-history-of-system-shock/ |archive-date=January 13, 2013 |url-status=live  }}</ref> This was confirmed by ''Dead Space'' designers, Ben Wanat and Wright Bagwell who stated that it was originally intended to be ''[[System Shock 3]]'' before the release of ''[[Resident Evil 4]]'' inspired them to go back to the drawing board and develop it into something more along those lines.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.pcgamer.com/how-resident-evil-4-turned-system-shock-3-into-dead-space/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=January 18, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118193608/http://www.pcgamer.com/how-resident-evil-4-turned-system-shock-3-into-dead-space/ |archive-date=January 18, 2017 |url-status=live  }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Glen Schofield and Michael Condrey at the Sledgehammer Games headquarter -- 21 October 2009.jpg|thumb|[[Glen Schofield]] and [[Michael Condrey]] were main creators of ''Dead Space'']]\n\nThe game's executive producer, [[Glen Schofield]] said that the team aimed to create something \"darker and creepier\" than their previous titles: \"We are all such huge fans of the [[horror fiction|horror]] and [[Science fiction|sci-fi]] genres. We wanted to create the most terrifying game that we could and keep the player on the edge of their seat the entire time.\"<ref name=\"gamespyannouncement\">{{cite web| title = EA Announces New Sci-Fi Survival Horror Title| work = Gamespy.com| publisher = IGN Entertainment| date = September 24, 2007| url = http://uk.xbox360.gamespy.com/xbox-360/dead-space/822686p1.html| access-date = June 24, 2008| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080914182936/http://uk.xbox360.gamespy.com/xbox-360/dead-space/822686p1.html| archive-date = September 14, 2008| url-status = live| df = mdy-all}}</ref> The design team reportedly spent time analyzing a wide variety of horror films in order to find inspiration for in-game scares.<ref name=\"ignfirstlook\">{{cite web | last = Haynes | first = Jeff | title = Dead Space First Look | work = IGN.com | publisher = IGN Entertainment | date = October 9, 2007 | url = http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/825/825875p1.html | access-date = May 20, 2008 | archive-url = https://www.webcitation.org/68DDIaW0Z?url=http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/825/825875p1.html | archive-date = June 6, 2012 | url-status = live | df = mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe previews drew attention to the high levels of gore and violence in the game, in particular the tactic of \"strategic dismemberment\", emphasized by Schofield as \"the primary theme of ''Dead Space''\".<ref name=\"gamespypreview1\" /> The Necromorphs could not be subdued by a single shot. They have to be incapacitated by shooting their tentacles and appendages off. A series of developer diaries released for the game featured one episode about the system which the developers mentioned that using conventional tactics such as aiming for the head or torso would only serve to aggravate some of the Necromorphs.<ref name=\"eurogamerpreview1\">{{cite web| last = Fahey| first = Rob| title = Dead Space Preview| work = Eurogamer.net| publisher = Eurogamer Network Ltd.| date = February 8, 2008| url = http://www.eurogamer.net/article.php?article_id=92372| accessdate = June 24, 2008| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20081207105121/http://www.eurogamer.net/article.php?article_id=92372| archive-date = December 7, 2008| url-status = live| df = mdy-all}}</ref> In order to make the corpses look more realistic, the development team studied the photos of the car crash victims<ref name=\"edgedeadspacecorpses\">{{cite web |title=Dead Space Team Studied Car Crash Victims |publisher=Edge-Online |date=October 14, 2008 |url=http://www.next-gen.biz/news/dead-space-team-studied-car-crash-victims |accessdate=October 19, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101028040328/http://www.next-gen.biz/news/dead-space-team-studied-car-crash-victims |archivedate=October 28, 2010  }}</ref> and war scenes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.edge-online.com/features/glen-schofield-writes-edge/|title=Glen Schofield Writes for Edge|work=Edge Online}}</ref>\nThe game was initially in development for the original [[Xbox (console)|Xbox]] console.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.destructoid.com/altman-be-praised-here-s-what-dead-space-looked-like-for-the-original-xbox-121520.phtml | title = Altman be praised: Here's what Dead Space looked like for the original Xbox console | access-date = August 28, 2010 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110709015941/http://www.destructoid.com/altman-be-praised-here-s-what-dead-space-looked-like-for-the-original-xbox-121520.phtml | archive-date = July 9, 2011 | url-status = live | df = mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Audio===\n{{Main|Dead Space Original Soundtrack}}\n''Dead Space'' credits two people for the music composition. Audio Director Don Veca was quoted in an interview saying \"The music credits read 'Music Composed and Conducted by [[Jason Graves]] in Association with [[Rod Abernethy]].' Early on, Rod was involved in initial brainstorming, but Jason actually composed, conducted and arranged all of the music.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Dead Space Sound Design |url=http://www.originalsoundversion.com/?p=693 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120905111334/http://www.originalsoundversion.com/?p=693 |url-status=dead |archive-date=September 5, 2012 |date=August 22, 2008 |accessdate=October 7, 2008 }}</ref> On November 11, 2008, Amazon.com and [[iTunes]] released the soundtrack of ''Dead Space'' for download.\n\nIn 2009, ''Dead Space'' was nominated for several awards by the non-profit Game Audio Network Guild (GANG): Music of the Year, Audio of the Year and Sound Design of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Good Music: 7th Annual Game Audio Network Guild Finalists Announced |url=http://www.destructoid.com/good-music-7th-annual-game-audio-network-guild-finalists-announced-121874.phtml |date=February 16, 2009 |accessdate=July 14, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110709015946/http://www.destructoid.com/good-music-7th-annual-game-audio-network-guild-finalists-announced-121874.phtml |archivedate=July 9, 2011 }}</ref> By the voting of the GANG members, ''Dead Space'' was awarded Audio of the Year and Sound Design of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dead Space Enjoys Audio Awards Hoard |url=http://www.next-gen.biz/news/dead-space-enjoys-audio-awards-hoard |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120917213102/http://www.next-gen.biz/news/dead-space-enjoys-audio-awards-hoard |url-status=dead |archive-date=September 17, 2012 |date=March 31, 2009 |accessdate=July 14, 2009 }}</ref>\n\n===DRM===\nThe retail PC version of ''Dead Space'' uses [[SecuROM]] copy protection as it was seen in the other EA PC titles ''[[Spore (2008 video game)|Spore]]'' and ''[[Mass Effect (video game)|Mass Effect]]'' which requires online authentication.<ref>{{cite web|title=Why does everyone say the PC controls are crappy?|url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/boards/949616-dead-space/45962019?page=2|publisher=gamefaqs|accessdate=July 26, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140328041100/http://www.gamefaqs.com/boards/949616-dead-space/45962019?page=2|archive-date=March 28, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> Previously, it limited the number of times that a user could install the game to five. However, in April 2009, the company released the de-authorization tools which afforded an unlimited number of installations.<ref name=\"neodeauth\">{{cite web | last = Ridgeley | first = Sean | title = EA releases new game De-Authorization Tools | work = neoseeker.com | publisher = Neo Era Media, Inc. | date = May 1, 2009 | url = http://www.neoseeker.com/news/10301-ea-releases-new-game-de-authorization-tools/ | access-date = November 16, 2009}}</ref> The [[Steam (software)|Steam]], [[Origin (digital distribution software)|Origin]] and [[Impulse (software)|Impulse]] versions do not have this DRM.\n\nOn July 14, 2016, [[GOG.com]] released a DRM-free version.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gog.com/news/dragon_age_origins_dead_space_simcity_3000_now_available|title=Dragon Age: Origins, Dead Space, SimCity 3000 now available! - GOG.com|website=www.gog.com|access-date=July 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing and release==\n[[Electronic Arts]] and [[Image Comics]] announced a comic book series based upon the game on February 21, 2008. Illustrated by [[Ben Templesmith]] and written by [[Antony Johnston]], the six-book [[Dead Space (comics)|''Dead Space'' comics]] are a prequel to the game. Set on Aegis VII, the planet that the USG ''Ishimura'' is orbiting, the deep space mining colony pulls an ancient artifact called \"The Marker\" from the planet which begins to affect everyone in the colony. The first issue was released on March 3, 2008. However, a limited edition version of issue #1 with exclusive cover art was made available at [[WonderCon]] 2008 to the first 25 people who went to the convention each day.<ref name=\"teamxbox1\">{{cite web|last=Berardini |first=C\u00e9sar A. |title=Dead Space Comic Book Announced |work=TeamXBox.com |publisher=IGN Entertainment |date=February 21, 2008 |url=http://news.teamxbox.com/xbox/15775/Dead-Space-Comic-Book-Announced/ |accessdate=June 24, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080509124424/http://news.teamxbox.com/xbox/15775/Dead-Space-Comic-Book-Announced/ |archivedate=May 9, 2008  }}</ref>\n\nElectronic Arts and [[Starz Media]] also announced an animated film, ''[[Dead Space: Downfall]]'', a prequel to the events of the game, taking place after the Necromorphs invaded the USG ''Ishimura''. The film, developed by Film Roman was released on October 28, 2008.<ref name=\"blog_ule\" />\n\nElectronic Arts released an Ultra Limited Edition of the game limited to only 1,000 copies. The package includes the game, ''Dead Space: Downfall'', a bonus content DVD, the ''Dead Space'' art book, a lithograph and the ''Dead Space'' comic.<ref name=\"blog_ule\">{{cite web|url=http://deadspace.ea.com/blogs/blog-en-us/archive/2008/09/25/ben-swanson-the-ultra-limited-edition-is-here.aspx|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081001073732/http://deadspace.ea.com/agegate.aspx?returnURL=%2Fblogs%2Fblog-en-us%2Farchive%2F2008%2F09%2F25%2Fben-swanson-the-ultra-limited-edition-is-here.aspx|archivedate=October 1, 2008|title=Ben Swanson: The Ultra Limited Edition is Here!|date=September 26, 2008|accessdate=October 21, 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref> The people who bought the game within the first two weeks of it's release could also download the exclusive suits for free: The Obsidian Suit for the PlayStation 3 version and the Elite Suit for the Xbox 360 version.<ref name=\"kotaku_suits\">{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/5057428/dead-space-gold-platform-exclusive-suits-for-launch-players|title=Kotaku: Dead Space Gold, Platform Exclusive Suits For Launch Players|date=October 1, 2008|accessdate=October 1, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081003210458/http://kotaku.com/5057428/dead-space-gold-platform-exclusive-suits-for-launch-players|archive-date=October 3, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nInitially, ''Dead Space'' Community Manager Andrew Green stated that Germany, China and Japan banned the game. However, it was confirmed that this was a marketing ploy and that ''Dead Space'' was not banned in any country.<ref>{{cite web |last=Plunkett |first=Luke |url=http://kotaku.com/5112903/so-dead-space-was-banned-well-nowhere |title=So Dead Space Was Banned, Well, Nowhere&nbsp;\u2014 Dead Space |publisher=Kotaku |date=December 17, 2008 |accessdate=July 25, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090319054918/http://kotaku.com/5112903/so-dead-space-was-banned-well-nowhere |archive-date=March 19, 2009 |url-status=live  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamepolitics.com/2008/09/05/report-dead-space-banned-germany-china-japan |title=Report: Dead Space Banned in Germany, China, Japan |date=September 5, 2008 |accessdate=October 24, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081013130205/http://www.gamepolitics.com/2008/09/05/report-dead-space-banned-germany-china-japan |archivedate=October 13, 2008  }}</ref>\n\nItalian Horror Director [[Dario Argento]] lent his voice to the Doctor Terrence Kyne character for the Italian release of the game.<ref name=\"wired_blog_argento\">{{cite news|url=http://blog.wired.com/games/2008/09/dario-argento-j.html|title=Wired Blog Network: Dario Argento Joins Italian Dead Space|date=September 26, 2008|first=Earnest|last=Cavalli|accessdate=October 27, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081105102210/http://blog.wired.com/games/2008/09/dario-argento-j.html|archive-date=November 5, 2008|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===''No Known Survivors''===\nOn August 22, 2008, ''No Known Survivors'', a website that was similar to an [[alternate reality game]] that provides an opportunity for the visitors to explore the narrative world of ''Dead Space'' was launched.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.noknownsurvivors.com |title=[EA&#93; Dead Space |publisher=Noknownsurvivors.com |accessdate=June 6, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130113102039/http://www.noknownsurvivors.com/ |archive-date=January 13, 2013 |url-status=live  }}</ref> The site depicts two stories, each divided into four chapters and uses 3D animations, voice acting, original video, Papervision 3D technology and various other interactive components.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dead Space Expanded |url=http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/902/902628p1.html |date=August 22, 2008 |accessdate=August 22, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080902200456/http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/902/902628p1.html |archive-date=September 2, 2008 |url-status=live  }}</ref> The first, ''Misplaced Affection'' tells the story of an organ replacement technician who falls in love with a capable P-Sec officer and slowly loses his sanity as the Necromorphs attempted to break the door to his shelter down. The second, ''Thirteen'' follows a [[sleeper agent]] who \"makes the wrong decision for the right reason\", set after Isaac launches the distress beacon. The site is less like a typical alternate reality game and more like a PC [[adventure game]] such as ''[[Myst]]''.\n\nThe site is based around a hub featuring nine severed body parts which represents a content release. The week before a content piece was released, it's assigned body part would mutate, finally evolving into a mature Necromorph part. Starting on August 25 and ending the week of the PC release, a new Necromorph part became active every Monday, allowing the visitors to continue the stories that are featured on No Known Survivors up until ''Dead Space'''s release. Following the release of ''Dead Space'', 94 prize winners were awarded a copy of the game on a platform of their choosing while 5 prize winners were awarded the limited collector's edition of the game and one grand prize winner was awarded the limited edition of the game in addition to a life-sized replica of Isaac Clarke's level three RIG helmet.\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n<!--Formatting-->\n| state = <!--plain/collapsible-->\n| align = <!--left/right/none/inherit-->\n| GR = (X360) 89.07%<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerankings.com/xbox360/943338-dead-space/index.html|title=Dead Space (Xbox 360)|publisher=[[GameRankings]]|accessdate=August 15, 2010|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/68DDiJ86Z?url=http://www.gamerankings.com/xbox360/943338-dead-space/index.html|archive-date=June 6, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref><br />(PS3) 89.05%<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerankings.com/ps3/943339-dead-space/index.html|title=Dead Space (PlayStation 3)|publisher=[[GameRankings]]|accessdate=August 15, 2010|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/68DDhiETD?url=http://www.gamerankings.com/ps3/943339-dead-space/index.html|archive-date=June 6, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref><br />(PC) 85.32%<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerankings.com/pc/949616-dead-space/index.html|title=Dead Space (PC)|publisher=[[GameRankings]]|accessdate=August 15, 2010|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/68DDis9mW?url=http://www.gamerankings.com/pc/949616-dead-space/index.html|archive-date=June 6, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| MC = (X360) 89/100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-360/dead-space|title=Dead Space (Xbox 360)|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=August 15, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110926120840/http://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-360/dead-space|archive-date=September 26, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref><br />(PS3) 88/100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-3/dead-space|title=Dead Space (PlayStation 3)|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=August 15, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100818014425/http://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-3/dead-space|archive-date=August 18, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref><br />(PC) 86/100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/dead-space|title=Dead Space (PC)|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=August 15, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110830195656/http://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/dead-space|archive-date=August 30, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| 1UP = B+<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.1up.com/do/reviewPage?cId=3170597&p=4&sec=REVIEWS |title=Dead Space Review |publisher=1up.com |date= |accessdate=October 17, 2008}}</ref>\n| CVG = 9.1/10<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/article.php?id=199245 |title=Review: Dead Space&nbsp;\u2014 ComputerAndVideoGames.com |publisher=Computerandvideogames.com |accessdate=October 17, 2008 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/68DDQhtET?url=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/199245/reviews/dead-space-review/ |archive-date=June 6, 2012 |url-status=live  }}</ref>\n| Edge = 8/10<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.next-gen.biz/reviews/dead-space-2-review |title=Review: Dead Space&nbsp;\u2014 EDGE Magazine |publisher=edge-online.com |accessdate=November 13, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606101629/http://www.next-gen.biz/reviews/dead-space-2-review |archivedate=June 6, 2011  }}</ref>\n| EuroG = 7/10<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eurogamer.net/article.php?article_id=259466 |title=Dead Space Review&nbsp;\u2014 Page 1 // Xbox 360 /